During a White House press briefing, Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics including the Dow Jones Industrial Average breaking through 25,000 for the first time, President Trump's economic agenda, responsible immigration reform, and the release of a controversial book about the Trump administration. Sanders also mentioned that the President believes in enforcing federal law, including laws regarding marijuana, and that the White House is focused on policy and moving the country forward. She criticized the book, calling it full of false and fraudulent claims, and stated that the President's attorneys are handling any potential legal action.